T -
All Implemented Interfaces:
DynLayout<T>
public final class DynLayoutImpl<T>
extends AbstractDynAttributeCheck<T>
implements DynLayout<T>

DynLayoutImpl implements the interface DynLayout and provides method to store dynamic visualization information in the form of intervals DynInterval stored in the interval tree DynIntervalTree. For each node we store a series of intervals corresponding to its x and y positions in time. The interval tree guarantees that the write and read operation to update the visualization are minimal and asynchronous.

Author:
Sabina Sara Pfister
